BFN 

  [Text] Revolutionary Armed Forces and Interior Ministry 
[Minint] distinguished service medals have been presented to a 
group of young soldiers who, on 27 May, prevented five 
individuals from hijacking a fishing boat and taking it to the 
Yankee base. 
  The medals were presented to Minint noncommissioned officers 
Misael Valentin Furnier, who is recovering from the gunshots 
received during the operation, and Norberto Duran, as well as 
civilian Arnel Lopez, captain of the hijacked boat. Ensign David 
Antonio Casamayer and soldiers Idilio Vargas, Jose Alexander y 
Sada, Rafael Montero, Giosvani Barrios, and Andres Solano, all 
members of the Border Guard troops, were also presented medals. 
  Juan Carlos Robinson, member of the Central Committee and 
first secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba in Guantanamo, 
stressed the bravery of the young soldiers and their attitude 
toward those who tried to violate Cuban law. 

